SELF-PROCLAIMED Queen of Kwaito, &ldquo;Mshoza&rdquo;, real name Nomasonto Maswanganyi, is said to have left ANN7&rsquo;s Football Extra producers hanging!The Abantu Bam hitmaker allegedly failed to pitch, when she was supposed to appear on the show, last month.A station insider said:&ldquo;To drop the interview at the last minute was highly unprofessional. This might negatively impact on her future interviews.&rdquo;&nbsp;Another source said Mshoza needed to mend her relationship with the media.&ldquo;She can&rsquo;t be a bad girl all her life. Her latest single is proof she has it in her to bring back the original kwaito sound that people fell in love with.&ldquo;It&rsquo;s a chance to revive her music career &ndash; that took a back seat after all the personal drama she was known for,&rdquo; said the second source.The mole added that Mshoza didn&rsquo;t even bother explaining, as she let her team do the cancelling.But Mshoza explained her side of the story to the SunTeam: &ldquo;They told me on Saturday &ndash;&ensp;which was one day before the show, which was aired on the Sunday.&nbsp;&ldquo;They also gave me two time slots, and so I ended up not knowing which show I was supposed to go in for.&nbsp;&ldquo;I think the initial person they wanted to interview dropped them &ndash;&ensp;and I was their plan B.&nbsp;&ldquo;It&rsquo;s really not my fault that the situation ended up like this,&rdquo; she said.ANN7&rsquo;s Moegsien Williams couldn&rsquo;t be reached for comment.Mshoza is making a career comeback, and has been getting gigs since the release of her single. Her next album will be out before long. She&rsquo;s a partner in a happy traditional marriage to successful businessman, Thuthukani Mvula.